sql:
SELECT robot_class, entry_fee
FROM robot_classes
WHERE is_active = 1 AND waiting_list > 10;

SELECT difficulty_level
FROM robot_classes
WHERE category = 'Combat';

SELECT * 
FROM participants 
WHERE robot_class_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "enthusiasts" refers to the participants registered in the robot classes;
- The term "top three" means the robot classes with the highest number of participants within each category;
- "participant counts" refers to the total number of participants in each robot class.

sql:
SELECT robot_class, currently_registered
FROM robot_classes
WHERE currently_registered = (
    SELECT MAX(currently_registered)
    FROM robot_classes
);

external_knowledge:
- 'Captains steering the most sails' refers to organizers with the highest number of events logged;
- 'Contact details' include name and email;
- 'Size of their fleets' indicates the number of team members.
